I"D<p>A new feature is included in the 3.5 version that makes it possible for you to set your website in multilingual.</p>

<p><strong>To activate Multilingual Mode:</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>Go to <strong>Admin Panel</strong></li>
  <li>Select <strong>Settings</strong> -&gt; <strong>Regional</strong></li>
  <li>Set <strong>Multilingual</strong> option to <strong>ON</strong></li>
  <li>Set your <strong>website languages</strong> (a language must correspond to the ones listed on <strong>Settings</strong> -&gt; <strong>Translations</strong>). Keep in mind that you need to push enter after each language.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Save</strong> button</li>
</ol>

<p>Once enabled you will see on your website a language selector.</p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/multilingual-configuration.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/multilingual-configuration.png" alt="multilingual configuration" />
</a></p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/multilingual-selector.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/multilingual-selector.png" alt="multilingual selector" />
</a></p>

<p><strong>Translate categories and locations:</strong></p>

<p>Once the multilingual mode is enabled you can update your categories and locations to translate their names and descriptions.</p>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/multilingual-translate-categories-locations.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/multilingual-translate-categories-locations.png" alt="multilingual translate categories and locations" />
</a></p>

